         UPDATED=20030917
           SPELL=PEAR-System_Command
        WEB_SITE=http://pear.php.net/package/System_Command/
      LICENSE[0]=PHP
           SHORT='PEAR: PEAR::System_Command is a commandline execution'
cat << EOF
System_Command is a commandline execution
interface.

Running functions from the commandline can
be dangerous if the proper precautions are
not taken to escape the shell arguments
and reaping the exit status properly.  This
class
give a formal interface to both, so that
you can run a system command as comfortably as
you would run a php function, which full
pear error handling as results on failure.
EOF

source $SCRIPT_DIRECTORY/../PEAR_DETAILS
